0:What Nishijou-kun had just said was very reasonable.\p;
100:It was strange, though.\n;It had made me feel... lonely.\n;There was this... heartrending pain in my chest.\p;
200:In the end, I had never been afforded the opportunity to confirm whether or not he was “Shogun.”\n;Maybe he had been telling the truth, and I was the one who'd gotten it all wrong.\p;
300:But even if I wasn't wrong, there was no point in holding a grudge against him now.\p;
400:If only I hadn't asked Yua-chan to switch places with me back then... If only I had just gone to the offline meet myself... then Yua-chan would still be alive.\p;
500:Yua-chan hadn't deserved to die. She'd had so many friends... our parents had loved her more than anything... and she'd been the smartest, most beautiful girl I'd ever met.\p;
600:And yet, she had died anyway.\n;Kusunoki Yua had died anyway.\p;
700:And when she had, Kusunoki Mia had disappeared along with her. She'd vanished into thin air, becoming a ghost.\n;That was the choice I had made back then.\p;
800:I could no longer tell whether I was alive, or dead.\n;All I knew... was that Yua-chan wasn't here anymore.\n;So I'd rather be dead.\p;
900:I stood at the edge of the helipad...\p;
1000:...where Yua-chan and the other four had jumped off that night.\p;
1100:Looking down made me feel dizzy.\n;The whole nightscape was pitch black. All the lights in the city had gone out, and yet, even in that darkness, I could still tell just how high up I really was.\p;
1200:I wondered how Yua-chan had felt when she'd jumped off of here.\n;She had probably been terrified.\p;
1300:I'm sorry, Yua-chan. I'm sorry you had to go through something so terrifying because of me.\p;
1400:<i>I</i><i>'</i><i>l</i><i>l</i> <i>b</i><i>e</i> <i>g</i><i>o</i><i>i</i><i>n</i><i>g</i> <i>t</i><i>o</i><i>o</i><i>,</i> <i>v</i><i>e</i><i>r</i><i>y</i> <i>s</i><i>o</i><i>o</i><i>n</i><i>.</i>\p;
1500:I will take the pain that you endured, the pain that I alone was supposed to feel, and engrave it onto my body, Yua-chan.\p;
1600:I took a deep breath.\n;My heart and mind were at peace.\n;I wasn't afraid of dying.\p;
1700:I spread my wings.\n;My arms lay in the empty air.\n;I closed my eyes.\p;
1800:And then, I stepped forward.\n;Into the bottomless abyss before me.\p;
1900:And with nothing there to support me anymore...\p;
2000:I fell.\p;
2100:My whole world turned upside down.\p;
2200:There was nothing left to chain me back.\p;
2300:Even though I was in free fall, it almost felt like I was floating.\p;
2400:Floating amid the rumbling of the wind.\p;
2500:The ground was rushing toward me.\n;The very same asphalt that Yua-chan had crashed into two months back. The hardened tar that had crushed her bones, ruptured her organs, and sprayed her blood and gray matter across itself.\p;
